Harbor Installation
	1.	From NKP Dashboard - Management Cluster Workspace - Applications
	2.	In Application - change all categories to general
	3.	Enable CloudNativePG
	4.	Using k8s dashboard see the deployment finished and success
	5.	Confirmed in Management Cluster - Applications - CloudNativePG is “Deployed” —> not “Enabled”
	6.	Enable Harbor - Choose “Rook Chef” as S3 Object Store
	7.	Using k8s dashboard see the deployment finished and success
	8.	Confirmed in Management Cluster - Applications -  Harbor is “Deployed” —> not “Enabled”
	9.	From Bastion —> kubectl get secrets -n ncr-system harbor-admin-password -o jsonpath='{.data.HARBOR_ADMIN_PASSWORD}' | base64 -d
	⁃	H6djLg=on1xchNfP2xZg
	10.	From Management Cluster - Application Dashboard - Harbor —> Click Dashboard
	11.	Login to harbor —> username: admin & password: (as mentioned above)
	12.	Select Administration - Users —> Click New User
	13.	Enter information:
	⁃	username	: nutanix
	⁃	email		: nutanix@nutanix.com
	⁃	Firstname	: nutanix
	⁃	password	: [your nutanix cluster password]
	⁃	confirm		: [your nutanix cluster password]
	⁃	Save
	14.	Click your new username and mark it as ADMIN
	15.	Logout  and login again as new user 
	16.	Configure and Create Docker Proxy Cache Registry 
	⁃	From Harbor Dashboard - Administration - Registries - New Endpoint
	⁃	Provider	: Docker Hub
	⁃	Name		: Docker Hub
	⁃	Access ID	: [your docker username]
	⁃	Secret	: [your docker password]
	⁃	Verify Cert	: Checked
	⁃	Click Test Connection —> “Connection tested sucessfully”
	⁃	Click OK
	⁃	From Harbor Dashboard - Project - New Project
	⁃	Project Name	: proxy_cache
	⁃	Access Level	: Unchecked Public
	⁃	Click the Proxy Cache slider and then select your registry endpoint —>  Docker Hub-https://hub.docker.com
	⁃	Click OK
	17.	Check docker login and docker push from BASTION VM
	⁃	Get harbor address
	⁃	export HARBOR_ADDRESS="$(kubectl -n kommander get kommandercluster host-cluster -o jsonpath='{.status.ingress.address}')"
	⁃	echo $HARBOR_ADDRESS 
	⁃	mkdir /etc/docker/certs.d/$HARBOR_ADDRESS:5000
	⁃	cd /etc/docker/certs.d/$HARBOR_ADDRESS:5000
	⁃	cat ca.crt
	⁃	sudo systemctl restart docker
	⁃	docker login -u nutanix -p nx2Tech806! https://10.38.13.140:5000/ —> must be “Login Succeeded”
	⁃	docker pull 10.38.13.140:5000/proxy_cache/goharbor/harbor-core:dev
	⁃	docker pull 10.38.13.140:5000/proxy_cache/hello-world:latest
	⁃	docker image ls 
	⁃	docker tag 10.38.13.140:5000/proxy_cache/hello-world 10.38.13.140:5000/library/hello-world
	⁃	docker image ls
	⁃	docker push 10.38.13.140:5000/library/hello-world
	⁃	from harbor dashboard examine
	⁃	Projects - proxy_cache - repositories
	⁃	Projects - library - repositories

